725896f-b.text:
150th Street, west side, between Sutter Avenue and Rockaway Boulevard, showing Public School No. 45. The original schoolhouse is the frcme building, facing on 150th Street, and the brick structure is a new addition facing on 149th Street, here seen from Sutter Avenue. View 2 shows the old school building which was later (1931 map) moved down about 150 feet to the northwest corner of Sutter Avenue. In its place was erected a new three-story building which was added to the brick
building seen in vlew 1.
MA, kw-.2wV
P. L. Sperr  March 15, 1927
NO REPRODUCTIONS  Views 1,2
